A DEADLY cholera outbreak sweeping through eastern and southern Africa has left 19 people dead, most of them in Tanzania.Angola has been the second-worst affected by the epidemic, with five deaths from 68 cases.In Tanzania, the cholera outbreak started in 2015 with 823 reported cases.Last year, 208 people died from 14 928 confirmed cases in the country. A total of 24 732 cases and 383 deaths have been reported there since the outbreak in August 2015.In Angola, the outbreak in Soyo, north-west of the country, spread to Cabinda, north of the Congo River with a total of 146 cases reported in the last two months.In Mozambique, six cholera cases were reported during this period, but there have been no deaths so far. &ndash; CAJ NEWS